    Class and Description

    This event causes the provider of an I/O resource to close (shut down) the resource.
    Eos
    This event signals the end of data from a stream.

    This event signals that a new chunk of data has successfully been obtained from some source.

  • Classes in org.jgrapes.io.events used by org.jgrapes.io 
    Class and Description
    Eos
    This event signals the end of data from a stream.
    Input
    This event signals that a new chunk of data has successfully been obtained from some source.
    NioRegistration 
    NioRegistration.Registration 
    Output
    This event signals that a new chunk of internally generated data is to be forwarded to some destination.
    SaveInput
    Causes the FileStorage component to write the data from all Input events on the channel that this event is fired on to a file until an Eos event is sent on the channel.
    SaveOutput
    Causes the FileStorage component to write the data from all Output events on the channel that this event is fired on to a file until an Eos event is sent on the channel.
    StreamFile
    Causes the content of a file to be streamed as a sequence of Output events (terminated by an Eos event) on the channel that this event is fired on.
